   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>XII.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE ISSUES OF THE GLORIFICATION OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Father's house in 14:2, the vine in 15:5, and the child in 16:21, which imply the Body of Christ, are all the issues of this glorification of Christ through His death unto resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>XIII.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>GOD BEING GLORIFIED IN CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>AND IN THE CHURCH</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God is glorified in Christ and in the church in the church age Eph 3:21 .</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>If we are not a part of the church, we will miss this glorification.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>XIV.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>EXPRESSING GOD IN OUR BEHAVIOR</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>When the believers express God in their behavior, God is glorified Matt 5:16 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>XV.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>BEARING MUCH FRUIT</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>When the believers as the branches bear much fruit, the Father is glorified John 15:8 .</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The more fruit we bear, the more God is glorified in our Christian work.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>XVI.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>BEING GLORIFIED IN THE KINGDOM AGE</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The believers who suffer with Christ in this age will be glorified in the kingdom age, that is, will reign with Him as His co-kings Rom 8:17; 2 Tim 2:12; Rev 20:4, 6 .</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>XVII.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>PETER'S MARTYRDOM</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Peter was martyred so that God would be glorified John 21:19 .</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>The Lord Jesus predicted this to Peter.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>XVIII.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>THE GLORY OF THE NEW JERUSALEM</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Eventually, all of God's chosen people will participate in the glory of the New Jerusalem, that is, will be glorified with the glory of God for eternity Rev 21:11 .</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>We need to enjoy what Christ is and live Him.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Eventually, we will be eternally glorified in His glorification.</S>
   </TEXT>
